Now I'm concerned about out-of-tree modules calling `do_trace_write_msr` directly, because it's EXPORT_SYMBOL. Without checking `tracepoint_enabled`, they'll take the SRCU lock and iterate an empty list. Well, out-of-tree modules are on their own, shouldn't block kernel optimization.

